headline: Dollar General earnings: Inventory has been a priority amid tariffs
summary: Dollar General (DG) is getting a stock boost on Tuesday morning after the discount retailer topped its first quarter earnings estimates and raised its annual guidance. RapidRatings Executive Chair James Gellert — who has given Dollar General's financial health a rating of 64 out of 100, above the broader retail space's rating of 55 — comes on the show to speak more about the chain's outlook and inventory management amid tariff concerns. Competitor Dollar Tree (DLTR) are scheduled to report its earnings this week on Wednesday, June 4. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here.
